  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">In 1979, Lusztig proposed a cohomological construction of supercuspidal representations of reductive p -adic groups, analogous to Deligne–Lusztig theory for finite reductive groups. In this paper we establish a new instance of Lusztig's program. Precisely, let D be the quaternion algebra over a local non-Archimedean field K of positive characteristic, and let X be the p -adic Deligne–Lusztig ind-scheme associated to <math altimg="si1.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><msup><mrow><mi>D</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>×</mo></mrow></msup></math> . There is a natural correspondence between quasi-characters of the (multiplicative group of the) unramified quadratic extension of K and representations of <math altimg="si1.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><msup><mrow><mi>D</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>×</mo></mrow></msup></math> given by <math altimg="si2.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mi>θ</mi><mo stretchy="false">↦</mo><msub><mrow><mi>H</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>i</mi></mrow></msub><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>X</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo stretchy="false">[</mo><mi>θ</mi><mo stretchy="false">]</mo></math> . We show that this correspondence is a bijection (after a mild restriction of the domain and target), and matches the bijection given by local Langlands and Jacquet–Langlands.</subfield>
